the Church of the Healing Christ (part of the Church of Divine Science), where Emmet Fox had become minister in 1931.\r\nIn the mid 1940s, he moved to Los Angeles, where he met Religious Science founder Ernest Holmes and was ordained into Religious Science by Holmes in 1946, thereafter teaching at the Institute of Religious Science. A meeting with Divine Science Association president Erwin Gregg led to him being preordained into Divine Science and he became the minister of the Los Angeles Divine Science Church in 1949, which he built into one of the largest New Thought congregations in the country. In the next decade, Murphy married, earned a PhD in psychology from the University of Southern California and started writing. After his first wife died in 1976, he remarried to a fellow Divine Science minister who was his longstanding secretary. He died in 1981.','Believe in Yourself (Hardcover Library Edition)','Believe in Yourself by Dr. Joseph Murphy, first published in 1955, shows you how the power of believing in yourself will help you achieve your dreams. He illustrates his points with wonderful stories about how inventors, writers, artists and entrepreneurs have used this power to reach the highest of heights. The book has proved highly motivational and has enabled many readers to overcome low self esteem and achieve their objectives in life. The author points out various ways by which one can overcome defeat, hardships and keep on the righteous track to succeed by using only fair means.','publish','open','closed','','believe-in-yourself-hardcover-library-edition','','','2021-12-08 09:31:58','2021-12-08 09:31:58','',0,'http://localhost/wp/wordpress/?post_type=product&#038;p=363',0,'product','',0),(364,1,'2021-12-03 07:07:24','2021-12-03 07:07:24','','book','','inherit','open','closed','','book-2','','','2021-12-03 07:07:24','2021-12-03 07:07:24','',363,'http://localhost/wp/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/book.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(365,1,'2021-1